data.description: Nestled just .7 miles from public beach access on Oak Island, this charming home epitomizes comfort and coziness with its inviting, open layout. Step onto the covered front porch for moments of relaxation or unwind on the rear open deck overlooking the serene backyard. This location is a haven for outdoor enthusiasts, being in proximity to the kayak launch into the Davis Canal, the Recreation Center, and the Scenic Overlook Trail. Discover the convenience of living near various amenities, including Publix Supermarket, a variety of restaurants, ice cream shops, local shops, the 55th Street Boat Ramp, and Middleton Park which offers several recreational activities and entertainment options. Oak Island boasts an impressive 65 public beach accesses, easily accessible pedestrian friendly sidewalks, several public fishing/crabbing docks, and numerous opportunities for outdoor recreation. Conveniently located to the historic waterfront town of Southport, cultural offerings of Wilmington and shopping and entertainment of Myrtle Beach. Don't miss out on the chance to experience the best of Oak Island living!
